g.text: START
input
Horrific Necktie: *Bratan*, now is the time!
You: Necktie, you and I are done. Both professionally -- and as friends. Begone! (End the tie.)

Horrific Necktie: The lifeless necktie looks like a colourful intestine of some dead animal: oily, alien and otherwise disgusting. What could have driven a man to wear something so repulsive around his neck?

Horrific Necktie: Cleansed by the blue spirit-fire of 98.7% pure alcohol, the fabric looks almost new again. No longer like a disgusting worm of the lower intestine, but like a colourful and deadly poisonous reef-snake of the Insulindian ocean.
You: So... what next?
Horrific Necktie: The necktie floats in the blueish liquid with almost unearthly grace.
Kim Kitsuragi: "That makes two of us." He shakes his head slowly. "Let's not waste any more time under this boardwalk. We need to clear this all up... somehow."
You: "Why not, lieutenant?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right. Okay. Anyway, I'm glad you told me your necktie has been speaking to you. That must not have been easy." For a second it looks like he's about to add something...
You: Necktie... I'm sorry. I didn't mean it like that.
Horrific Necktie: No, *bratan*, no need for that. You and I are *bratannoi* -- brothers. Brothers fight. But when they're done fighting, you know what they do? They party. They fucking party!
Kim Kitsuragi: "No harm? In drinking 98.7% alcohol with a god-knows-how-old tie in it? I wouldn't be so sure." The lieutenant tilts his head slightly. "However, I'm not here to judge. Let's go."
spirithub
You: Wait, right now? A woman just died and you think now is a good time to party?
You: Wait, right now? Ruby's gone. I don't really think there's anything to celebrate here.
You: You know what, I'm done with this crazy talking necktie bullshit!
You: Slowly uncork the blue medicinal spirit.
Horrific Necktie: Now, *bratan*, take me off.
You: What? I didn't know I could do that...
You: Take the necktie off.
You: "Okay, Kim... I didn't want to tell anyone, but my necktie has been talking to me lately."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Of course it has." He doesn't even look too surprised.
You: But that's *too much fun*.
Horrific Necktie: Just put me in the bottle, *bratan*. I'm not gonna let you down. You and I are, like, the same person.
Horrific Necktie: First, the spirits -- the blue medicinal spirits. Grab the bottle and uncork it! It is time to unleash the Other-World.
Horrific Necktie: The bottle opens with a silent, mysterious hiss. The fumes rising from its mouth are as crisp as the northern winds.
Shivers: Howling somewhere, lashing the boardwalk with brine and rain -- an ancient warmth crawls under your skin.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant has been observing you quietly all this time.
Empathy: He's struggling to keep silent, but finally seems to give up.
Esprit de Corps: We're all under stress. This is turning into a great big mess. I'm not judging. Just keep it together.
Kim Kitsuragi: ...but then he turns away -- his gaze fixed on the road ahead. "Let's go," he concludes.
You: Okay, then tell me -- it is time for what?
Horrific Necktie: Oh... you will see. (It feels like the tie is rubbing itself against your chest like a cat in heat.)
Electrochemistry: Yeah... what's the problem here?

Horrific Necktie: Why shouldn't there be a party when you die? And, beside, this isn't even about that! You have no idea what this is about... this is gonna be so off the hook. It's gonna be off *all* hooks.
Conceptualization: It's like an organic sample brought back from a distant star system inhabited by sentient neckwear.
You: Cork the bottle and put it away.
IsKimHere()
Kim Kitsuragi: "That makes absolutely no sense." He thinks for a moment. "But I guess every family has its own traditions."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let us not linger. We have a great big mess to figure out." He turns to face the road ahead.
You: "Signs of some really hard core mental illness, Kim." (Point to your head.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "I would assume, yes. Why did you put it in the bottle?"
You: Time for what?
You: Go away necktie. You're just a figment of my imagination.
Horrific Necktie: *Bratan*, don't push me away. I want to be there for you. Also -- how can you be sure *you* are not just a figment of *my* imagination?
You: Get lost, necktie! I don't want to be your friend.
You: Begone, foul necktie! Finally I rid myself of you! (End it. Throw the necktie as far as you can.)
Horrific Necktie: The oily rag flaps miserably in the air and lands close by in the dirt. It looks like an inanimate object, completely devoid of life.
You: "It started when I woke up in the Whirling-in-Rags. It's been talking to me ever since."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And what has the necktie been telling you, if I may ask?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "A relationship between a man and a talking necktie? No, apparently I am not." His voice rings of insincere sadness as he turns to leave.
You: Now what?
Horrific Necktie: Now put me in the bottle.
Inland Empire: It was just trying to help....
Horrific Necktie: As the necktie slides into the purifying liquid, large stains of grease rise off from it and float to the surface. There they quickly dissolve and disappear completely.
You: Necktie?
Horrific Necktie: There is silence.
You: "I don't really know, but I'm eager to find out."
You: "In my family, you put a piece of clothing in some hard liquor and drink it for good luck. It's silly, but no harm done, right?"
You: "It teaches me about life, Kim. Sort of a father figure."
You: "It mostly urges me to party harder."
You: "We're buds. Mostly just goofing around."
Horrific Necktie: Feels good. Feels safe.
Jump to: [You: "Necktie, you and I are done. Both p..."]
Horrific Necktie: *Bratan*, have I ever lied to you? Just take me off. (The necktie tugs encouragingly at your neck.)
Horrific Necktie: Your fingers manage to undo the oily knot and the necktie slides off. It looks so frail sitting there in your hand, weighing almost nothing.
You: Put the necktie tie in the bottle.
Inland Empire: Seems you'll never learn the answer to that question.
Horrific Necktie: *Bratan*, life and death are inseparable. There's a party when you're born, a party every year to celebrate that birth, and a party when you're put in the ground.
You: But... why?
Horrific Necktie: Trust me -- just trust me. You and I are going to have so much fun it should be illegal!
You: I suspect that it might be.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay. So why did you put it in the bottle?"
You: "I simply don't know."

Horrific Necktie: Hush-hush, *bratan*, now is not the time to celebrate, now is the time to get *ready*. Trust me on this. This is what it's all been building towards. It's gonna be off the hook. Off *all* hooks.
You: "Because it told me to."
Horrific Necktie: But, *bratan*... no. Please uncork it. I can make it good again.
You: "Forget it, you're not *open-minded* enough to understand anyway."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Wonderful. Very useful."
Rhetoric: He doesn't actually believe it's wonderful.
Drama: As always -- lie.
Untitled hub
Horrific Necktie: But, *bratan*... I... I understand. (The tie loosens around your neck.) I just wanted you to have fun. I... I never meant to be a burden.
You: "In my family when someone dies you put a piece of clothing in a bottle as a sign of eternal respect."

You: "Mind your own business, binoclard!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I've got to ask..." he says, a peculiar look in his eyes. "What are you doing?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Alright." The lieutenant's face stiffens as he turns to look at the road ahead. "I won't ask again."
